subject: Skip glean-install for ironic ramdisks
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2023-11-03 19:46:22.000000000', 'files': ['diskimage_builder/elements/simple-init/install.d/50-simple-init'], 'message': "Skip glean-install for ironic ramdisks

When ironic-python-agent-builder is in the mix, we are building
a ramdisk which *likely* shouldn't have simple-init's glean run
on boot because the ramdisk, if being used with simple-init,
may encounter cases where DHCP-less deployments are being
performed, and prior configuration drives may be discovered
on the host.

Ironic's agent has code to determine if the device is valid or not,
and will soon handle re-initalizing it for the purposes of safely
initalizing networking as a backport enabling for safe handling
and determination of the correct device to utilize.

This change, just skips glean-install from being triggered in the
image build and logs a message to that effect.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/ironic-python-agent/+/895519
Closes-Bug: 2032377
Change-Id: I3c6e0538f3a404fb9138366cb163aa6b49b880ff
"}]
commit_message:
Skip glean-install for ironic ramdisks

When ironic-python-agent-builder is in the mix, we are building
a ramdisk which *likely* shouldn't have simple-init's glean run
on boot because the ramdisk, if being used with simple-init,
may encounter cases where DHCP-less deployments are being
performed, and prior configuration drives may be discovered
on the host.

Ironic's agent has code to determine if the device is valid or not,
and will soon handle re-initalizing it for the purposes of safely
initalizing networking as a backport enabling for safe handling
and determination of the correct device to utilize.

This change, just skips glean-install from being triggered in the
image build and logs a message to that effect.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/ironic-python-agent/+/895519
Closes-Bug: 2032377
Change-Id: I3c6e0538f3a404fb9138366cb163aa6b49b880ff

commit_message:
Allow domain admin to view roles

Domain admins are allowed to assign roles. So it should be allowed to
view roles.

Note that protection job is made non-voting until the domain admin role
test cases are updated.

Closes-Bug: #2059780

commit_message:
Retire devstack gate

This "removes" devstack-gate content in order to retire it. Devstack
grew the ability to bootstrap its own CI environments using ansible and
no longer needs devstack-gate.

Part of the motivation for this chagne is that it will help us in our
quest to remove old Ubuntu Xenial test nodes from the CI system as
devstack-gate still relies on them.

commit_message:
Don't create an OVSDB connection per API request

Using the default ovsdbapp.backend.ovs_idl.Backend behavior which
stores the ovsdb_connection on the Backend class itself ensures
that when Octavia does the imports necessary for instantiating the
driver, that the ovsdb_connection will remain on the class even
though the instances are deleted. This will allow us to reuse the
OVSDB connection between APIs despite octavia-api knowing nothing
about it.

In addition, __del__() can called from any thread by the garbage
collector, and so it was possible that thread.join() would be
called by the thread we were in, throwing an Exception and
preventing cleanup.

Co-authored-by: Gregory Thiemonge <gthiemon@redhat.com>
Co-authored-by: Ihar Hrachyshka <ihrachys@redhat.com>
Co-authored-by: Jakub Libosvar <jlibosva@redhat.com>

Closes-Bug: #2065460
Closes-Bug: #2065459

Change-Id: I4f5df34ab32e8b33ff54f311b9b2ac00c9be1e05

commit_message:
Implement variables to address oslo.messaging improvements

During last release cycle oslo.messaging has landed [1] series of extremely
useful changes that are designed to implement modern messaging
techniques for rabbitmq quorum queues.

Since these changes are breaking and require queues being re-created,
it makes total sense to align these with migration to quorum queues by default.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/q/topic:%22bug-2031497%22

Change-Id: Ia0d7ac84ced77511b82f28e409477e4d1589adb6

commit_message:
Add variable to globally control notifications enablement

In order to be able to globally enable notification reporting for all services,
without an need to have ceilometer deployed or bunch of overrides for each
service, we add `oslomsg_notify_enabled` variable that aims to control
behaviour of enabled notifications.

Presence of ceilometer is still respected by default and being referenced.

Potential usecase are various billing panels that do rely on notifications
but do not require presence of Ceilometer.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-ansible-plugins/+/914144
Change-Id: I9efc107116b149b75b2ed8b54335758e57d6dabc

commit_message:
Allow additional load balancer customisation

Changes the 'octavia_provider' label to also apply to OpenStack Cloud Controller Manager load balancers (to address the issue raised in [1]). Also adds support for the 'octavia_lb_algorithm' and 'octavia_lb_healthcheck' cluster labels to improve feature parity with Heat driver.

[1] https://github.com/stackhpc/magnum-capi-helm/issues/54

Change-Id: I41c9c1ae31dfbe390d533ba94b15da7a285e84f6
